These are two made-for-TV movies, the movie Bill and it&amp;#039;s sequel Bill: On His Own, both starring Mickey Rooney.

Bill  1981 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0082075/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0082075/&lt;/a&gt;
From the DVD jacket -
Based on a true story, Mickey Rooney gives an Emmy Award winning performance as Bill, in the highly acclaimed, moving and inspirational story of a 40 year old mentally retarded man with an I.Q. of 50, unable to read or write, living in the brutal rough and tumble of New York City.  He must learn the ways of the city or face going back to the institution in which he spent the better part of his life.  Bill is kind-hearted, warm and friendly but his childlike innocence gets him in trouble.  Barry Morrow (Dennis Quaid), an amateur documentary filmmaker, befriends and enables Bill to learn about family and true friendship.

Micky Rooney won:
- 1982 Emmy &quot;Outstanding Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Special&quot;
- 1982 Golden Globe for &quot;Best Performance by an actor in a Mini Series or Motion Picture Made for TV&quot;

The Movie &quot;Bill&quot; won
- 1982 Emmy for &quot;Outstanding Writing in a Limited Series or a Special&quot;
- 1982 Golden Globe for &quot;Best Mini-Series or Motion Picture Made for TV&quot;
- 1982 Peabody Award

Mickey Rooney, Dennis Quaid, Largo Woodruff, and Anna Maria Horsford

